definition.value: A mannosylated ceramide phosphoinositol compound having a hexacosanyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very long chain fatty acid.
The dihexadecyl ester of phosphoric acid.
Insoluble fibrous protein aggregates exhibiting beta sheet structure.
A phosphatidylglycerol in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.
A phosphatidic acid in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.
A phosphatidylcholine in which the phosphatidyl acyl groups are both oleoyl.
A univalent carboacyl group group formed from nucleophilic cleavage of the beta-lactam ring of aztreonam.
A phosphatidylglycerol consisting of cardiolipin lacking one fatty acyl group from the 2 or 2'-position.
A phosphatidylglycerol consisting of cardiolipin lacking two fatty acyl groups from the 2 and 2'-positions.
A polysaccharide derivative composed of a backbone of linear derivatised-tetrasaccharide repeating units that are joined to each other via beta-(1->6)-linkages.

A univalent carboacyl group formed by loss of OH from the carboxy group of 2-(2-hydroxyphenyl)-4,5-dihydro-1,3-thiazole-4-carboxylic acid; an intermediate of pyochelin biosynthesis (bound to carrier protein).
A polysaccharide composed of a backbone of branched pentasaccharide repeating units that are joined to each other via alpha-(1->2)-linkages.

A mannosylated ceramide phosphoinositol compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

A mannosylated ceramide phosphoinositol compound having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain-base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.
A dodecasaccharide comprising two branched hexasaccharide units joined via a beta-(1->2) linkage. Part of the lipopolysaccharide obtained from Salmonella serogroup C1.
A polysaccharide composed of a backbone of linear trisaccharide repeating units that are joined to each other via alpha-(1->2)-linkages; corresponds to the O repeating unit of Salmonella serogroup E.
An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen.
An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen.

A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide compound having an inositol 1-phosphoryl group attached to the mannose residue and a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, with no hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a hexacosaonyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, with no hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and no additional hydroxylation of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and no additional hydroxylation of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a tetracosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.

An inositol phosphomannosylinositol phosphoceramide compound having a hexacosanoyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen, hydroxylation at C-4 of the long-chain base, and hydroxylation at C-2 and C-3 of the very-long-chain fatty acid.
A phosphorylated mannosylinositol compound which constitutes the head group of some mannosylinositol phosphorylceramides (the MIPCs), and is a product of their catabolism.
A phosphorylated mannosylinositol compound which constitutes the head group of some mannosylinositol phosphorylceramides (the M(IP)2Cs), and is a product of their catabolism.
A dihydroceramide having at least one glycosyl group attached to either of its hydroxy groups.
A 2,3-diacyl-1-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 2- and 3-positions are oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A metalloporphyrin consisting of coproporphyrin III with a central iron atom.
A 1,2-diacyl-3-alpha-D-galactosyl-sn-glycerol in which the groups at the 1- and 2-positions are linoleoyl and oleoyl respectively.
An oxidised form of cardiolipin, usually arising from either chemical or enzymic oxidation of any C=C double bonds in the phosphatidyl acyl groups.
A reduced form of cardiolipin, usually arising from hydrogenation of any C=C double bonds in the phosphatidyl acyl groups.
Ethylbenzene in which the pro-R alpha-hydrogen is substituted by the nitrogen at the 1 position of 1H-imidazole-5-carboxylic acid. Its ethyl ester, etomidate, is used as an intravenous anaesthetic.
A decaprenyl diphosphate having (Z)-stereochemistry in all but one of the double bonds.
A tridecaprenyl diphosphate having two (E)- and ten (Z)-double bonds.
A dodecaprenyl diphosphate having two (E)- and nine (Z)-double bonds.
A tetradecaprenyl diphosphate having two (E)- and eleven (Z)-double bonds.
Zwitterionic form of 4-amino-4-deoxy-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl ditrans,polycis-undecaprenyl phosphate having an anionic phosphate group and a protonated amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A tridecaprenyl diphosphate having three (E)- and seven (Z)-double bonds.
A L-galactose 1-phosphate compound having beta-configuration about the anomeric centre.
Zwitterionic form of any peptide where, in general, the amino terminus is positively charged and the carboxy terminus is negatively charged.
A dipeptide comprising D-serine with a D-alanyl residue attached to the alpha-nitrogen.
An undecaprenyl phosphate having two (E)- and eight (Z)-double bonds.

A malonate ester that is diisopropyl malonate in which the two methylene hydrogens at position 2 are replaced by a 1,3-dithiolan-2-ylidene group. An insecticide and fungicide used to control a range of diseases including Pyricularia oryzae, Helminthosporium sigmoideum and Fusarium nivale.
The trianion arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate hydroxy groups and the imide nitrogen of 6-hydroxy-FAD.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside 5'-diphosphate obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups of 2'-deoxyuridine 5'-diphosphate (dUDP).
A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate having eleven prenyl units and 4-amino-4-deoxy-alpha-L-arabinopyranosyl as the glycosyl moiety.
